extent.value: in one record carton, six manuscript boxes, one oversize flat box, and one oversize folder.

abstract.value: Nancy Fales Garrett is a writer, director, and teacher. This collection contains original manuscripts of theater pieces, poem, short stories, a novel, published pieces, critical reviews, posters, slides, and photos related to Garrett's works.

p.value: Materials are open to researchers. Please contact the Fales Library and Special Collections, fales.library@nyu.edu, 212-998-2596.

Published citations should take the
following form:<lb/><lb/>
Identification of item,  date (if known); Nancy Fales Garrett Papers; MSS 51; box number; folder number; Fales Library and Special Collections, New York University Libraries.
Donated to the Fales Library by Nancy Fales Garrett.

Nancy Fales Garrett is a writer, director, and teacher.  Fales Garrett began her theatrical career at LaMaMa ETC and later founded Shakespeare in the Valley, a Shakespeare workshop for teenagers.  Fales Garrett's plays include <emph render="italic">Arc, Playing in Local Bands, Some Sweet Day, The Northern Kingdom,</emph> and <emph render="italic">Dora</emph>.  In addition, Fales Garrett has written the screenplays <emph render="italic">The Stranger</emph> and <emph render="italic">The Northern Kingdom</emph> and been awarded playwriting fellowships from NYSCA and the National Endowment for the Arts.  Fales Garrett teaches playwriting at St. Ann's School in Brooklyn, NY.

The Nancy Fales Garrett Papers include original manuscripts of theater pieces, poem, short stories, a novel, published pieces, critical reviews, posters, slides, and photos related to Garrett's plays.
